	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001584_0001"/><!--pb/@n='01'-->
<lb/><p rend="center"><term type="ailment">Fever</term> Powder</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Take of Resin of <term type="plant">Jalap</term> 
<lb/>and Calomel of each eight grains 
<lb/>Quinine &amp; <term type="plant">Rhubarba</term> of each 
<lb/>four grains - mix well together, 
<lb/>and when needed, make into 
<lb/>pills with spirit of cardamoms
<lb/>Dose from (10) ten to (20) twenty 
<lb/>grains - The mixture keeps 
<lb/>best in powder -</p>
<lb/><p>If the violent symptoms 
<lb/>are not relieved in from four 
<lb/>to six hours by the operation 
<lb/>of the pills a dessert spoonful 
<lb/>of <placeName><settlement type="town">Epsom</settlement></placeName> <term type="foodstuff">salts</term> may be taken
<lb/>Then quinine in four or six 
<lb/>grain doses completes the cure
<lb/>It is usually given till the ears 
<lb/>ring or <term type="ailment">deafness</term> is produced</p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><placeName><settlement type="town"><choice><orig>Tette</orig><reg>Tete</reg></choice></settlement></placeName> <date when="1860-11-26">26<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> <choice><abbr>Nov<hi rend="sup">r</hi></abbr><expan>November</expan></choice>
<lb/>1860</date> <space extent="2" unit="words"/><del type="strikethrough">For</del></p>
			
